Text.Value: I came on the myconid sovereign's behalf. It demands revenge.

Text.Value: I see your idiocy is only surpassed by your ego.
You command with the gravitas of a spoiled child. Pathetic.
Finish the slaves, True Soul. For the Absolute.
You been a shit since I laid eyes on you, red-eye. Go on, try and gut me. I ain't going down easy.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: To Nere. Brithvar pulls out a dagger and points it at Nere.

EditorData.logicalname: Mind meld - said in your mind

Text.Value: Heretics. Let Nere be your end.

EditorData.NodeContext: Drugh = FUCK. DROOG (like food, not hood)

Text.Value: If you'd listened to those gnomes, maybe you wouldn't have been trapped.
You bargained with this wretch? How vexing.
... yet a True Soul still lives. I am sure there's a sane explanation.
Those duergar were thorns in our sides, so I removed them.
Side with Brithvar and the rebels.
This battle will make a good story. Come, then.
The only weakness I see here is you.
Say nothing.
You dare speak to me without due reverence? That was your first and last mistake.
Bloody hells, had enough of your shit.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to Nere. Pulls out dagger and points it at Nere.

Text.Value: ... you've one final chance to prove your allegiance.
And yet I don't care a jot for you. Now that's curious.
The myconid sovereign wants the rot cleansed - and you're last on the list.
It's true - you did your best.
... yet the faithless yet stand. Isn't that right, Brithvar?
Thrinn. Carve out her heart and serve it to the rothé.
Thrinn. Carve out his heart and serve it to the rothé.
Thrinn. Carve out their heart and serve it to the rothé.
You so much as touch me, and I'll tear you from limb to limb.
*Nere sifts through your memories - and a new presence clouds your mind. The duergar elder.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: You, Nere, and Brithvar grip your heads in a mindmeld. Nere senses Brithvar through you.

Text.Value: *Your scalp buzzes as Nere's mind reaches out - not to you, but to the duergar elder.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Nere and Brithvar experience a mindmeld.

Text.Value: Yet the Absolute saw fit to bless you? I don't understand...
A slave uprising. They slaughtered every last one of their masters.

Text.Value: Try it. I'll cut you all down.
The outsider did me a favour. The duergar were trouble from the start.
True Soul - prove your faith. Strike him down.
If it means getting paid, my blade's yours!
Worthless slaves. Your incompetence has been my ruin.
The slavers turned on each other - mutineers versus Absolute loyalists.
I only see weakness in the cowardly slaver standing before me.
*Your head tingles as Nere scans the room.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Nere holds his hand to his head as he mentally scans the room.

Text.Value: Nere is not without mercy, True Soul. The rat has given you a chance to earn my favour.
So you say. And yet the Absolute demands that I cull them.
A test - yes, you must be. The Absolute bade you to try Nere's faith.
Strike them down. Prove your faith.
As for you, our charge is clear - there is more we must do.
If she indeed is a True Soul, let the Absolute save her.
If he indeed is a True Soul, let the Absolute save him.
If they are indeed a True Soul, let the Absolute save them.
You're damned right I'll have it. Me and that one, we got a deal. We beat your arse and dig the dues out from your carcass.

Text.Value: I won't do it.
Damn it. I'll rip your flesh clean off!
For the Absolute!
In your eulogy, I'm going to call you a 'Twat-Soul'.
*A fire blazes in your head, then spreads through your blood.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Nere's eyes widen. He is on to your lie.

Text.Value: Side with Nere and the Absolutists.
Traitor. You have breathed your last!
... they've outlived their usefulness.
Try winning the argument by yourself, why don't you. It'll build character.
Damn right it's time. You owe my crew a tenday's worth o' coin, Nere - and the reckoning's come.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Brithvar pulls out his dagger and points it at Nere.

Text.Value: Nere will not be refused!
Damn right I'll have it - straight off your rotted corpse.
You wouldn't dare. I'm faithful to the Absolute.
Attack Brithvar and the duergar rebels.
I don't care about your squabble. I just want Nere's head.
Do nothing.
Side with the duergar mercenaries.
Cast Detect Thoughts.
Brithvar. Did you think you could keep your plot a secret?

EditorData.logicalname: Mutineer quest not accepted - logic node needs to stay

Text.Value: Attack Nere.
Nere pities you, Thrinn. Your errors and excuses. And your sorry end.

Text.Value: I killed your friends - and you're next.
I act on orders of the Absolute.

Worthless, every last one. Their failures must be punished.

EditorData.logicalname: Mind meld - said in your mind

Text.Value: Drop the blade, duergar. You shall have your coin.
Nere. Does. Not. Fail.

EditorData.NodeContext: ZHIL loo-NIN! Rising, seething anger. Only the last word should be louder.

Text.Value: As you say. Ghil lu'nin!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Nere prepares to cast his spell

Text.Value: You heed an overgrown toadstool, yet defy a True Soul?

Says the idiot who got himself buried. Look at the stone - it was clearly a trap.
Your god. My oath. Let us see which prevails.
*Your skull buzzes, and you see your own face through Nere's eyes.*
You been a shit since I laid eyes on you, red-eye. Go on, try and gut me. I ain't going down easy.
Insufferable, insolent, scum. I'm going to enjoy this.
Fool. Your silence speaks to your heresy. For the Absolute!

EditorData.logicalname: Nere and players against all the duergar

Text.Value: An efficient solution. Sensible, even.
Vermin to the last. I might have guessed.

EditorData.NodeContext: Calling out in fear: his beloved is about to be executed

Text.Value: Shut your shitholes, both of yeh. You owe my crew a tenday's worth o' coin, Nere - and it's time you shell out.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Brithvar pulls out his dagger and points it at Nere.

Text.Value: Hells...

Nere is not without mercy, True Soul. These overgrown rats have given you a chance to earn my favour.
Useless!
*The elder's disgust grips your head like a vice - yet he remains silent.*

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Brithvar mindmelds with the player and gives them the side eye.

Text.Value: You were lazy, Thrinn. Without me, Nere would be dead.
Fool. Did you think I wouldn't notice your intrusion?

You care for the weak, True Soul. Most curious.
And yet you came to my aid.
Heathen. You shame the Absolute!
Attack the deep gnomes.
Touch another innocent and I'll take your head, Nere.
I'm not here to judge.
Strike him down. Prove your faith.
Side with Nere.
Shit.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Addressed to Nere. Pulls out dagger and points it at Nere.

Text.Value: The Absolute guides my hand. You've chosen a battle you cannot win.
You were left helpless by some rubble. You're hardly in a position to call anyone weak.
My head? I walk among traitors.
The Absolute demands their slaughter. Yet here you stand, in bold defiance.

Say nothing.
As for you, True Soul...
I will tear out your heart and feed it to the rats.
That's your cue, Brithvar. It's time you got paid.
Thrinn. The Absolute gave you everything. And this fiasco is how you reward Her?

Text.Value: But you are a traitor. And I will have your head!
Do nothing.
Vermin. As feral as they are useless.
You're the only one suffering today, Nere.
I'll offer up your guts, ingrates.

I don't know what you are, that you can defy the Absolute's will.

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Nere grips his head in a brief mind-meld, then releases it and frowns at player.

Text.Value: Finally.

EditorData.NodeContext: Said with great relief, but tinged with anger

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Nere fires off a spell, killing Beldron, and then the remaining gnomes.

Text.Value: You are a liar - and a fool. Nere suffers neither!
Me and mine worked flat out. I was cracking the whip day and night! Tell him, True Soul!
Hmm? What? Sorry, I wasn't paying attention.
Duergar - this True Soul has betrayed us. Let his blood prove your devotion!
Duergar - this True Soul has betrayed us. Let her blood prove your devotion!
Duergar - this True Soul has betrayed us. Let their blood prove your devotion!

Text.Value: Plant a thought in Nere's mind. 'The gnomes must be set free.'

Cut down the duergar - every last one. The Absolute commands it!

EditorData.CinematicNodeContext: Nere grips his head in a brief mind-meld, then releases it.

Text.Value: My cares are none of your concern.

The only head I mean to take is yours, Nere.

Gnomes, you are slaves no longer. The Absolute may have use for you yet.
You are a traitor.

Nere is your death. The Absolute wills it!

What is this, then? The Absolute's servants. Dead...
Your best was not good enough.

EditorData.logicalname: Nere and all duergar against player - Brithvar dead

Text.Value: Ah, so you didn't come to my aid. You came to theirs.
I'll slit your throats before you can blink.
You come turnin' my people, strikin' Thrinn dead - and you still ain't paid up. Shell it out, ya prickhole!

Synopsis: Dialogue after you destroy the cave-in and set Nere free. Thrinn has been put in charge of getting Nere out, but it's the player who accomplishes it. Nere almost just died from inhaling poisonous gas, so he's very angry. In this dialogue, you determine the fate of the gnomes as well as Nere and the mutinous duergar.
